ownedComment.body: This design pattern appears in Workstation Software Framework, SPIE 2008 located at: http://mbse.gfse.de/documents/SPIE-WSF-with-Copyright.pdf

mdElement.text: Fault Tolerant Sequencer pattern. While in the NOMINAL state external Event0, Event1, Event2, EventN execute the next ActionN() call on entry. Within ActionN() an internal Error event can be generated to exit from the NOMINAL state into an ERROR state where the error condition is logged and a Recover event can be generated that restores the original state within NOMINAL.
